question.text: The clitoris is a tiny finger-like structure, which lies at:

options.text: the upper junction of the two labia minora above the urethral opening.
the upper junction of the two labia minora below the urethral opening.
the lower junction of the two labia minora above the urethral opening.
the lower junction of the two labia minora below the urethral opening.

solution.text: The clitoris is the most sensitive and erogenous organ of sexual pleasure present in the female reproductive system. It contains a lot of nerve endings. It is homologous to the penis. Clitoris is present at the upper junction of the two labia minora above the urethral opening.
